name: f666 number 4, fall 2012
description:
F666 is proud to announce that issue number 4 is out today and ready for ordering! Number 4 has expanded 12 more pages with more columns, more interviews and more photographs! F666 number 4 features a Mutant Supremacy and Magrudergrind tour photo special series, Danielle 'Metalographer' Fedorshik's 6.66 reasons, an interview with Roberta Bayley about her iconic photograph of The Ramones in the 'Artist Behind The Cover' feature, columns about Henry Thoreau crust punkin', going to metal shows in the 90's and a critique of Until The Light Takes us. Lastly number 4 is chock full of photographs of Inquisition, Trenchgrinder, Psychic Limb, Immolation, Krallice, Mutilation Rites, Fuck the Facts and much, much more of the NYC metal and punk scene.
Full color zine. Fifty-two pages. Saddle stitched. 8.5" by 5.5" Limited 100 copies, 1st edition. Buy them locally! Available at Generation Records in New York City, Desert Island in Brooklyn and at the Visual and Critical Studies Library at the School of Visual Arts.
More images of the issue available here. Follow us on Facebook for updates!

name: f666 number 3, spring 2012
description:
f666: the metal, punk and hardcore photography zine is out now with number 3, Spring 2012 . This “special” is just in time for Maryland Deathfest season. Entitled ‘MDF: Death Metal Parking Lot’, this one features photos taken from four disposable 35mm cameras that captured the fest-goer’s in and around Sonar’s parking lot from the 2011 MDF.
Full color zine. Forty pages. Saddle stitched. 8.5" by 5.5" Limited 100 copies, 1st edition. Buy them locally! Available at Generation Records in New York City, Desert Island in Brooklyn and at the Visual and Critical Studies Library at the School of Visual Arts.
More images of the issue available here. Follow us on Facebook for updates!

name: f666 number 2, winter 2012
description:
f666 number 2, the metal, punk and hardcore photo zine is out! This one features a show photo diary by Nunslaughter, a photo contribution entitled '6.66 reasons' by Angela Boatwright, 'artist behind the cover' interview with Jon Clue, columns by select writers and my photo coverage of the numerous bands that come through New York City including Incantation, Cannibal Corpse, Coffinworm, Wormrot and much, much more. Pre-order here. A few copies of the first issue still remain and can be picked up here.

name: f666 number 1, fall 2011
description:
The inaugural f666 quarterly photo zine!
Available September 25th, 2011.
Featuring interviews with Karlynn Holland, contributing photography spread with Justina Villanueva, essays by Justin Elm and finally, Suren Karapetyan's photography coverage of the ever exploding metal scene in New York City.
Full color zine. Thirty six pages. Saddle stitched. 8.5" by 5.5" Limited 100 copies, 1st edition. Buy them locally! Available at Generation Records in New York City, Desert Island in Brooklyn and at the Visual and Critical Studies Library at the School of Visual Arts.
